    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      MagicSquare(int s, char d, java.lang.String init)
      Constructor method, first generates a matrix using s as the size, then assigns d as the filling direction and init as the initial filling position; validating each of the aforementioned parameters, and finally proceeds to fill the square using the method developed by Simon de la Loubère.

    • Constructor Detail

      • MagicSquare

        public MagicSquare(int s,
                   char d,
                   java.lang.String init)
            throws InvalidSizeException,
                   java.util.InputMismatchException
        Constructor method, first generates a matrix using s as the size, then assigns d as the filling direction and init as the initial filling position; validating each of the aforementioned parameters, and finally proceeds to fill the square using the method developed by Simon de la Loubère.
        Parameters:
        s - The size of the square to be created.
        d - The filling direction of the square to be created.
        init - The initial position of the filling process used in the square to be created.
        Throws:
        InvalidSizeException - Thrown whenever is attempted to create a square using an invalid size.
        java.util.InputMismatchException - Thrown whenever is attempted to create a square using either an undefined filling direction or initial filling position.

      • assignInitPos

        private void assignInitPos(java.lang.String init)

        Assigns the initial filling position of the square.
        Parameters:
        init - String containing the initial filling position of the square.
        Throws:

      • assignDirection

        private void assignDirection(char d)
                      throws java.util.InputMismatchException
        Assigns the filling direction of the square.
        Parameters:
        d - Filling direction to be assigned.
        Throws:
        java.util.InputMismatchException - Thrown when the character to be assigned as the direction does not match as any of the possible filling directions.

      • fillSquare

        private void fillSquare()
        Fills the square using the method published by Simon de la Loubère.

      • defineStartingPos

        private int[] defineStartingPos()
        Defines the starting position to be used in the filling process.
        Returns:
        A 4 positions integer array, with the starting vertical position in its first slot, the starting horizontal position in its second, the vertical growth in case the filling process encounters a number in its third and the horizontal growth in case the filling process encounters a number in its fourth slot.

      • defineGrowths

        private int[] defineGrowths()
        Assigns the increment vertically and horizontally in the magic square's filling process.
        Returns:
        A two positions array, containing the vertical growth in the first position and the horizontal growth in the second.
